script.name: tv.lu.cmd.dockagent
script.description: Cmd: Manages a dock by buying or selling wares

line.comment: * Command status code:
* Standby: Waiting for station stock to increase
* Station Agent: Searching for a deal
* Idle: No stations found
* Text: Buy or Sell
* Minimum profit to bother making a trade run
* 0 Level
* 1 XP
* 2 Pilot Original Name
* 3 Total commissions paid
* Time between checks when a station can't be found
* For now, price is just a paint in the ass, we'll take any price.
* If inCargo is greater than zero at this point, it means that the ship couldnt
* unload because the station was full, but the ship has the ware to sell in cargo
* This was where we checked for bulk equipment sell.
* RIP, bulk equipment sell
* $MainType = get maintype of ware $Ware
* Error -401 is a sale not found error. Were making the assumption that its due
* exclusively to the fact that the sale price is too high
* Error -106 is a no request amount. We're asking for load sell amount, meaning
* were loading what the station has free. If were getting 106, someone filled the
* sell station before we could get to it.
* = wait 200 ms
* $Source.MinimumThreshold = $SourceCurrent[1]
* This ware has been flagged for a delay
* We don't want to make a run for energy every single time someone moves, so..

line.text: 'BUG: dockagent %s no index found for dockwares '

line.comment: * = wait 200 ms
* This ware has been flagged for a delay
* If we can't make at least MinProfitRun credits on this run, fuck it.
* gosub BuyFightDrones:
* Testing Value:
* $WaitLength = 1000
* Checking to see if the station is paused.
* Non level adjusted wait times
* $FRQRequired = [THIS]-> get resupply fuel required
* Requires Return=amount sold
* Return is from a SellSpareEquipment command
* Return is from a Trade.Sell command
* play sample 1114
* Higher number will slow level progression
